      "acceptanceCriteria": "The continuum mechanics formulation, contact modeling approach, and material constitutive model are justified by prior literature and sensitivity analyses demonstrating that alternative model forms produce QoI differences within uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "A bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity model for Ti-6Al-4V is supported by published tensile coupon data and is consistent with prior FDA validation studies. Frictionless versus frictional contact sensitivity showed less than 3% QoI variation. The chosen model form is adequately justified for the COU. Achieved level meets required level."
