      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (elastic modulus, yield strength, tangent modulus) are sourced from lot-specific coupon testing or peer-reviewed literature with documented uncertainty bounds. Geometric inputs are derived from CMM measurements of the as-manufactured screw.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and yield strength for Ti-6Al-4V were taken from lot-specific tensile coupon data provided by DePuy Synthes (n=5 coupons per lot). Geometric dimensions were verified against CMM measurements within ±0.02 mm tolerance. Parametric uncertainty in material properties was propagated via a 50-sample Monte Carlo study. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples are production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws assembled with UHMWPE blocks per ASTM F1717. Sample size N=11 provides sufficient statistical power to characterize inter-specimen variability.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from production lots and tested per ASTM F1717. Sample size N=11 across two independent laboratories provides adequate coverage of manufacturing variability. All specimens were inspected for dimensional conformance prior to testing. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios, including at least two distinct axial load levels and two screw offset configurations representative of the intended surgical application.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single standardized ASTM F1717 load configuration (5.4 Nm offset, ambient conditions). No variation in offset distance, load rate, or environmental condition was explored. The single test condition does not span the clinical range of loading scenarios, leaving uncertainty in model extrapolation to other configurations. Achieved level (2) falls below the required level (3) for this model risk category."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions, loading) are demonstrably equivalent to the as-tested experimental conditions, with documented traceability for each parameter.",
      "rationale": "FEA geometry was reconstructed from CMM measurements of the tested specimens. Material properties in the model were set to the lot-specific coupon values. Boundary conditions replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture constraints as confirmed by fixture drawings. Load application matches the experimental protocol. Full input equivalency traceability matrix is documented. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
