      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 and percentage QoI difference < 10% for all three quantities of interest across all N=11 specimens.",
      "rationale": "For all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement), the normalized validation metric E/uval ranged from 0.31 to 1.44 across the 11 specimens, and percentage differences ranged from 1.2% to 8.7%. All comparisons satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The three validated QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements for the pedicle screw system.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the spine; yield force is the primary indicator of fatigue-relevant plastic deformation onset; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield energy absorption. All three QoIs are specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly relevant to the regulatory decision context. Achieved level meets required level."
